<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6916] Using markup in a GString causes a stack overflow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6916</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In a markup template, if you write something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;p &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;This is a ${strong(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;bold text&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the user will assume that the output is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;This is a &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;bold text&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the markup builder is a &lt;b&gt;streaming&lt;/b&gt; builder, so calling a method in a GString results in a direct rendering to the output. At best, it will trigger a NPE, or a stack overflow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest to add the following notation to allow that kind of code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;p &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;This is a ${$strong(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;bold text&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)}&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The inner tag is preceded with a dollar($) sign, which tells the markup engine that the call should be rendered as a string. It would be a shortcut notation for:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;p &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;This is a ${stringOf { strong(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;bold text&apos;&lt;/span&gt;) } }&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
